 15: 
 16: ## Schema Selection
 17: 
 18: ### Choose the Most Specific Type
 19: 
 20: Always use the most specific Schema.org type available:
 21: 
 22: **Good:**
 23: ```python
 24: # Use specific type for research paper
 25: doc = DocumentGenerator("ScholarlyArticle")
 26: ```
 27: 
 28: **Bad:**
 29: ```python
 30: # Using generic type
 31: doc = DocumentGenerator("CreativeWork")
 32: ```
 33: 
 34: ### Type Hierarchy
 35: 
 36: Understand the Schema.org type hierarchy:
 37: 
 38: ```
 39: Thing
 40: └── CreativeWork
 41:     ├── Article
 42:     │   ├── NewsArticle
 43:     │   ├── BlogPosting
 44:     │   └── ScholarlyArticle
 45:     ├── DigitalDocument
 46:     │   └── (Your files)
 47:     ├── MediaObject
 48:     │   ├── ImageObject
 49:     │   │   └── Photograph
 50:     │   ├── VideoObject
 51:     │   └── AudioObject
 52:     │       ├── MusicRecording
 53:     │       └── PodcastEpisode
 54:     ├── SoftwareSourceCode
 55:     └── Dataset
 56: ```
 57: 
 58: ### File Type Mapping
 59: 
 60: | File Extension | Primary Type | Alternative Types |
 61: |---------------|-------------|-------------------|
 62: | .pdf | DigitalDocument | Article, Report, ScholarlyArticle |
 63: | .jpg, .png | ImageObject | Photograph |
 64: | .mp4, .mov | VideoObject | MovieClip |
 65: | .mp3, .wav | AudioObject | MusicRecording, PodcastEpisode |
 66: | .py, .js | SoftwareSourceCode | - |
 67: | .csv, .json | Dataset | - |
 68: | .zip, .tar | DigitalDocument | Archive |
 69: 
