521: ## Common Pitfalls
522: 
523: ### Pitfall 1: Missing Required Properties
524: 
525: **Problem:**
526: ```python
527: doc = DocumentGenerator()
528: doc.set_basic_info("My Document")
529: # Missing encodingFormat - will fail validation
530: ```
531: 
532: **Solution:**
533: ```python
534: doc = DocumentGenerator()
535: doc.set_basic_info("My Document")
536: doc.set_file_info(
537:     encoding_format="application/pdf",  # Always include
538:     url="https://example.com/doc.pdf"
539: )
540: ```
541: 
542: ### Pitfall 2: Relative URLs
543: 
544: **Problem:**
545: ```python
546: img.set_property("contentUrl", "/images/photo.jpg")  # Relative URL
547: ```
548: 
549: **Solution:**
550: ```python
551: base_url = "https://example.com"
552: img.set_property("contentUrl", f"{base_url}/images/photo.jpg")
553: ```
554: 
555: ### Pitfall 3: Inconsistent Data
556: 
557: **Problem:**
558: ```python
559: # File says it's 100KB but schema says 50KB
560: file_size = os.path.getsize(file_path)  # 102400
561: doc.set_property("contentSize", "50000B")  # Wrong!
562: ```
563: 
564: **Solution:**
565: ```python
566: # Always use actual file data
567: file_size = os.path.getsize(file_path)
568: doc.set_property("contentSize", f"{file_size}B")
569: ```
570: 
571: ### Pitfall 4: Over-Nesting
572: 
573: **Problem:**
574: ```python
575: # Too many nested levels
576: doc.add_person("author", ...)
577: doc.author.add_person("mentor", ...)
578: doc.author.mentor.add_organization("employer", ...)  # Too deep!
579: ```
580: 
581: **Solution:**
582: ```python
583: # Keep it simple - 1-2 levels max
584: doc.add_person("author", "Jane Smith", affiliation="University")
585: ```
586: 
587: ### Pitfall 5: Not Validating Before Storage
588: 
589: **Problem:**
590: ```python
591: # Save without validation
592: schema = doc.to_dict()
593: database.save(schema)  # Might be invalid!
594: ```
595: 
596: **Solution:**
597: ```python
598: # Always validate first
599: schema = doc.to_dict()
600: validator = SchemaValidator()
601: report = validator.validate(schema)
602: 
603: if report.is_valid():
604:     database.save(schema)
605: else:
606:     handle_validation_errors(report)
607: ```
608: 
609: ### Pitfall 6: Ignoring Recommended Properties
610: 
611: **Problem:**
612: ```python
613: # Minimal schema - low quality
614: doc = DocumentGenerator()
615: doc.set_property("name", "Document")
616: doc.set_property("encodingFormat", "application/pdf")
617: # Nothing else!
618: ```
619: 
620: **Solution:**
621: ```python
622: # Include recommended properties
623: doc = DocumentGenerator()
624: doc.set_property("name", "Document")
625: doc.set_property("encodingFormat", "application/pdf")
626: doc.add_person("author", "Author Name")  # Recommended
627: doc.set_dates(created=datetime.now())  # Recommended
628: doc.add_keywords(["topic1", "topic2"])  # Recommended
629: doc.set_property("description", "Clear description")  # Recommended
630: ```
631: 
632: ### Pitfall 7: Wrong Date Formats
633: 
634: **Problem:**
635: ```python
636: # Non-standard date format
637: doc.set_property("dateCreated", "01/15/2024")  # US format
638: doc.set_property("dateCreated", "15-01-2024")  # EU format
639: ```
640: 
641: **Solution:**
642: ```python
643: # Use ISO 8601
644: from datetime import datetime
645: 
646: doc.set_dates(created=datetime(2024, 1, 15))
647: # Results in: "2024-01-15T00:00:00"
648: ```
